review_blob: Wowwee! Nice pour, thick rich head that lasts!Bigger nose than other wheats-hoppier, fruitier. Hazy golden brew. Full of flavor and zing on the tongue, yet virtually no aftertaste.  I taste wheat, peach, malt, nicely hopped. This is now at the top of my list. Definately a beer that rocked my world. A winner!

Deeper golden than some pilsners & I immediately notice the aroma, bigger nose than most I've tried lately. Subtle hop and a stronger malt fragrance. Virtually no head, though bubbly. A little lemon, rounder feel in the mouth. This is definately an easy drinker! Very refreshing! Too bad it's kinda expensive.  Gotta catch it on sale.

I like pouring this. "Unfiltered" means floaters! Head dissipates quickly. Subtle yeasty-citrusy aroma. I have this from bottle as often as from tap, but am rating a brew from the bottle. Taste is suprisingly smooth, just a little sparkle on the tongue. I usually have this one in the local establishments when there isnt a fabulous alternative, as its on tap everywhere in KC. Not my favorite, but a good standard for me!

Head forms white and frothy, then quickly dissipates. It did leave a nice lacey effect around my glass. Subtle aroma, just a hint of yeasty-citrus and hop. Flavor is even more subtle. Nothing standing out except a little sweetbread. Finishes clean. Pretty insubstantial, not as impressed as Id hoped.
Small average head,smooth golden color. Soft cracker aroma-more wheatthin than saltine. Subtle hop, pretty simple but well balanced.
Fizzy pour, champagne-like. nose of new spring grass, kinda florally, with just a hint of green apple.  Definately one of the more satisfying pilsners. Clean finish, crisp-Yummy!
